Hepatitis C virus","Hepatitis D virus","Hepatitis E virus","Hepatitis G virus"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatitis D virus\u003C/strong\u003E is a defective RNA virus that requires the presence of hepatitis B surface antigen (HBsAg) to enter hepatocytes and complete its life cycle. It can occur either as a co-infection (simultaneous infection with hepatitis B) or as a superinfection in people who already have chronic hepatitis B.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other viruses can all establish infection independently:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatitis A virus\u003C/strong\u003E is transmitted via the faecal-oral route\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatitis C virus\u003C/strong\u003E is transmitted via blood exposure\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatitis E virus\u003C/strong\u003E is transmitted via the faecal-oral route\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatitis G virus\u003C/strong\u003E (GB virus C) can replicate independently\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWithout hepatitis B virus co-infection, hepatitis D virus cannot complete its replication cycle as it requires hepatitis B viral proteins for viral assembly and secretion.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Hepatitis D virus is a defective RNA virus that requires hepatitis B surface antigen to enter hepatocytes and complete its life cycle.","Hepatitis D virus infection can occur either as a co-infection with hepatitis B or as a superinfection in chronic hepatitis B carriers.","Other hepatitis viruses (A, C, E, G) can establish infection independently without requiring co-infection."],"references":["Mehta P, Grant LM, Reddivari AKR. Viral Hepatitis. 2024 Mar 10. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32119436","Lok AS, Pawlotsky JM. Viral hepatitis at a crossroad. Gastroenterology. 2012 May;142(6):1261-3. doi: 10.1053/j.gastro.2012.03.007. PMID: 22537431","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53988"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15355"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53988","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53988"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-09T20:11:09+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-09T20:11:58+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8046"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68531"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4928","links":{"s